OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA mainly dry morning with some
OL,6,Fpatchy cloud. Sunny spells will
OL,7,Fdevelop, although theres a chance of
OL,8,Fa few showers around the Glasgow area,
OL,9,Fwhile Argyll is likely to stay mostly
OL,10,Fdry.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FAny showers will clear away
OL,13,Fthis evening. The rest of the night
OL,14,Fwill be dry with clear spells, perhaps
OL,15,Fmore cloud affecting the Glasgow area
OL,16,Flater on.
OL,17,
OL,18,CTuesday:FDry and settled with light
OL,19,Fwinds. Any early morning cloud will
OL,20,Fbreak up to leave a good deal of warm
OL,21,Fsunshine for the rest of the day.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
